This paper is about machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper describes a system that uses cross-lingual embeddings and neural machine translation to translate news articles from German to Czech. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. 

The paper also mentions the use of a tuned PBMT model, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the use of neural machine translation involves deep learning techniques, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). 

The paper also focuses on the handling of named entities, which is a sub-topic of NLP that falls under the category of natural language understanding (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of iterative back-translation, which is a technique used in information retrieval (cs.IR) to improve the quality of search results.
